metadata.name: GOLENS #89
metadata.description:
"- May every star in the sky become a life?"
"- Yes, and I'll call them golens!

Have you ever noticed how morbid it is? People make wishes to shooting stars. Do they not understand? What can a star, desperate, in the midst of a suicidal fall, give you? She just wants to die at ocean.

Tonight the stars will not fall, they will rise, and they'll be watching our end, we'll die in the ocean.


GOLENS are generative created.
- 15 Body Parts ( not on traits )
- 6 Hierarchy Grades.
- 9 Sky.
- 4 Weathers.
- 9 Powers.


by Gen Doodler | twitter.com/GenDoodler

metadata.description: Codename: Kids Next Door (also known as Kids Next Door and KND) is an American animated television series created by Tom Warburton (credited as "Mr. Warburton") for Cartoon Network, and the 13th of the network's Cartoon Cartoons. The series follows the adventures of a diverse group of five 10-year-old children who operate from a high-tech treehouse, fighting against adult and teen villains with advanced 2×4 technology. metadata.name: Extreme Ways #65
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features
Main features are listed : Main style, drawing style, etc…
I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…
Lots of parameters are used internally to ensure a large variety in the outputs.

metadata.name: KUNZ'S DREAM ᶠⁱˣᵉᵈ #56
metadata.description:
Tribute to the Swiss artist Emma Kunz (1892-1963). She rejected the idea of art versus non-art, and instead expanded her definition to include research, medicine, and nature, as well as the supernatural, magical, and visionary. Don't stop discovering her art!

This piece is inspired by her uncompromising handling of geometry and the colorful, freehand pictorial finish of her work, a sensibility with which I connect very deeply.

"KUNZ'S DREAM" is a generative piece of software coded using p5js by a biological intelligence.

(ᶠⁱˣᵉᵈ) Previous "KUNZ'S DREAM" token has some errors. Collectors who minted it, you have a reserve at your disposal.

metadata.name: odium #6
metadata.description:
The idea behind "odium" is to mix the two previous works to create a new art, which maintains similarities with the previous projects, but also with its differences and peculiarities.

"odium" is based on an algorithm that I've been exploring since the "radium" and "illusions" projects. So this is the last of the series.

It is composed by with grainy/noise and flowfields, creating a glitch effect as it is finishing to render.
"odium" have random colormaps instead a configured palette system, patterns of growth and plays with randomized blendModes and colorModes, 
and I name it "odium"  because the form it grows and glitch reminds me how the hate sometimes slowly consume the mind.

This is a project made in p5.js


Omar Lobato, 04/29/2022.

metadata.name: Colorfall #43
metadata.description:
My first attempt at a generative NFT. This started with an idea to create a grid of diagonal lines with the basic line function of p5js. I had discarded this idea until my friend said it looked like a waterfall of colors and he liked it, so I decided to mint it. After tweaking some parameters like colors and line thickness it produced some nice outputs.

I hope you will enjoy it. Free mint(unless you cant wait and want to pay =) plus 25% royalties for minters.

reserves for the collectors of my testnft on objkt, my friend CampendonkP and a few artists who I remembered who did free mints, like punevyr and JohnRising.

metadata.name: de|growth:generations #50
metadata.description:
Materials tend to take particular forms due to their physical properties, technological necessities or natural limitations. However, what rules should a simulated environment follow when no physical constraints are inherent to the digital environment?

This project continues the exploration of shaping digital matter that I began on hicetnunc in 2021. Each token creates an image of a unique sculpture generated with a custom growth/degrowth algorithm. The image is rendered with a tailored raytracing script.

---
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones for the 800x800px image.

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the resolution from preview quality to a print of approx. 30x30cm. There may be minor differences in tone or contrast for different resolutions.

In live mode:
Click PNG to save the rendered image.
Click STL to download the digital model to view on your computer or 3d print at home [experimental]

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #416
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.
